\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>), <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/ExistsUnique.html#ExistsUnique\">∃!</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/ExistsUnique.html#ExistsUnique\">:</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/ExistsUnique.html#ExistsUnique\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a property `P : α → β → Prop` such that for all `a : α`, there exists a unique `b : β`\nwith `P a b`, then `unique_choice_fun h` gives a function `α → β` selecting this unique `b` for\neach `a`. ","docLink":"./SDG/Axiom/UniqueChoice.html#unique_choice_fun","kind":"def","line":64,"name":"unique_choice_fun","sourceLink":"https://github.com/riccardobrasca/SDG/blob/3a3a575ea280340795f4069edd0a3f397c3ffe08/SDG/Axiom/UniqueChoice.lean#L64-L68"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./SDG/Axiom/UniqueChoice.html#unique_choice_unique\"><span class=\"name\">unique_choice_unique</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">P</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/ExistsUnique.html#ExistsUnique\">∃!</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Ex